'''Pavel Šulc''' (born 29 December 2000) is a Czech professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] for {{French football updater|Lyon}} club [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]] and the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic national team]].

Šulc made over 150 appearances for [[FC Viktoria Plzeň|Viktoria Plzeň]], and was named the [[Czech Footballer of the Year]] in 2025.

==Club career==
===Viktoria Plzeň===
Šulc was promoted to the first team of [[FC Viktoria Plzeň|Viktoria Plzeň]] in January 2020 but only played his first match on 17 January 2021 against [[FK Příbram]].<ref>{{Cite news|title= Příbram - Plzeň 0:0, další ztráta favorita, hosté nedali gól ani z penalty|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/prvni-liga/pribram-viktoria-plzen-fortuna-liga-15-kolo.A210115_105221_fotbal_jic|work=iDNES.cz|date=17 January 2021|access-date=27 November 2025|language=cs|publisher=Mafra|agency=[[Czech News Agency]]}}</ref>

Scoring once each season in [[2020–21 FC Viktoria Plzeň season|2020–21]] and [[2021–22 FC Viktoria Plzeň season|2021–22]],<ref>{{Soccerway|572021}}</ref> Šulc started the [[2023–24 FC Viktoria Plzeň season|2023–24 season]] with a [[hat-trick]] against České Budějovice.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Pavel|last=Kortus|title=Nejlepší zápas kariéry, liboval si Šulc. Na penaltu ho poslali spoluhráči|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/prvni-liga/plzen-budejovice-fotbal-zapotocny-hattrick-koubek-sulc.A230813_185929_budejovice-sport_pkr|work=[[iDNES.cz]]|publisher=[[Mafra (company)|Mafra]]|date=13 August 2023|access-date=22 April 2024|language=cs}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=Pavel Šulc zařídil hattrickem vítězství Viktorky v Českých Budějovicích|url=https://www.qap.cz/zpravy/zpravy-kraj/sport/clanek/pavel-sulc-zaridil-hattrickem-vitezstvi-viktorky-v-ceskych-budejovicich-129749/post-detail.htm|website=QAP|date=13 August 2023|access-date=22 April 2024|language=cs}}</ref> He contributed to Viktoria Plzeň's [[2023–24 UEFA Europa Conference League]] campaign, where they reached the quarter-final of a European competition [[FC Viktoria Plzeň in European football|for the first time]].<ref>{{Cite news|first=Zdeněk|last=Soukup|title=Asi jsme tu smlouvu s ďáblem podepsali jen na 90 minut, usmál se Šulc|url=https://plzensky.denik.cz/fotbal-prvni-liga/smlouvu-s-dablem-podepsali-pavel-sulc-viktoria-plzen-20240418.html|work=[[Deník]]|date=18 April 2024|access-date=22 April 2024|language=cs|publisher=[[Vltava Labe Media]]}}</ref>

===Loan spells===
On 29 January 2019, Šulc was loaned to [[FC Vysočina Jihlava]] in [[Czech National Football League]], playing he played in 16 league matches and scored 3 goals.

On 3 July 2019, he was loaned to [[SFC Opava]] in [[Czech First League]]. In six months long loan he played in 15 league matches and in 1 [[Czech Cup]] match without scoring a goal.

On 26 January 2020, he was loaned to [[SK Dynamo České Budějovice]] in Czech First League. In one year long loan he played in 15 league matches and scored 3 goals.

In June 2022, he joined Czech First League side [[FK Jablonec]] on a season-long loan, reuniting with manager [[David Horejš]] who he had worked with at České Budějovice in his previous loan spell.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Martin|last=Sedlák|title=Šulc si zažil krizi. Plzeňský talent hledá restart v Jablonci|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/prvni-liga/pavel-sulc-plzen-jablonec.A220623_670749_fotbal_ten|work=[[iDNES.cz]]|publisher=[[Mafra (company)|Mafra]]|date=23 June 2022|access-date=26 March 2025|language=cs}}</ref>

===Lyon===
On 4 August 2025, Šulc signed a four-year contract with [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]] in France.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Olympique Lyonnais|url=https://www.ol.fr/fr/actualites/arrivee-de-pavel-sulc-jusqu-en-2029|title=Arrivée de Pavel Šulc jusqu’en 2029|trans-title=Pavel Šulc's arrival until 2029|date=4 August 2025|access-date=4 August 2025|language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Čihák|first=Jiří|publisher=[[Mafra (company)|Mafra]]|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/zahranici/sulc-uz-patri-lyonu-smlouva-na-ctyri-roky-plzen-muze-dostat-az-ctvrt-miliardy.A250804_204841_fot_zahranici_jic|title=Šulc už patří Lyonu, uvedl se videem z holičství. Smlouvu podepsal na čtyři roky|trans-title=Šulc already belongs to Lyon, he announced with a video from the barbershop. He signed a four-year contract|date=4 August 2025|access-date=5 August 2025|language=cs|work=[[iDNES.cz]]|agency=[[Czech News Agency]]}}</ref>

==International career==
Šulc had played international football at youth levels that ranged from [[Czech Republic national under-18 football team|Czech Republic U18]] to [[Czech Republic national under-21 football team|U21]]. He played a total of 15 matches for the U18–U20 teams and scored four times. For the U21 team, he played in 20 matches and scored two times.<ref>{{cite web |title=Pavel Šulc|url=https://www.fotbal.cz/repre/hrac/hraci/16332707|publisher=[[Football Association of the Czech Republic]]|language=cs|access-date=24 March 2026}}</ref>

On 22 March 2024, Šulc debuted for the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech senior squad]] in a [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly match]] against [[Norway national football team|Norway]].<ref>{{Cite news|first=Tomáš|last=Petr|title=Máme lavičku, která fandí, chválí Hašek atmosféru v celém týmu. Rozhodování o Euru bude složité|url=https://www.irozhlas.cz/sport/fotbal/ivan-hasek-trener-reprezentace-reakce-po-priprave_2403271042_mim|publisher=[[Czech Radio]]|date=27 March 2024|language=cs}}</ref>

On 10 September 2024, Šulc scored his first goals for the Czech Republic, scoring twice in a 3–2 victory against Ukraine in the [[2024-25 UEFA Nations League B|Nations League]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Czechia vs. Ukraine - 10 September 2024 |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2024/09/10/europe/uefa-nations-league/czech-republic/ukraine/4319414/ |access-date=11 September 2024|work=Soccerway}}</ref>

